- "shine like stars" refers to products with high average ratings;
- "glowing customer ratings" refers to the average rating of the products;
- "frequent purchases" refers to the number of times the product has been purchased;
- "substantial revenue contributions" refers to the total revenue generated by the product.

- 'highly praised' refers to products with an average rating higher than the overall average rating of all products;
- 'shining brighter than the average star in the sky' is a metaphor for products with above-average ratings;
- 'wise shoppers' refers to customers who have purchased these highly rated products;
- 'treasures collected in their carts' refers to the total quantity of products purchased.

- "Top 5 products" refers to the products with the highest average ratings;
- "Average bust measurement" is calculated from the bust measurements of customers who have ordered the product;
- "Total number of reviews" is the count of reviews for each product.

- "top 3 products" refers to the products with the highest average order value;
- "average order value" is calculated by dividing the total order value by the number of orders;
- "customers who have made at least two purchases" implies a minimum of two orders.

- "generous patrons" refers to customers who have spent more than 100 on their orders;
- "threshold of 100 coins" refers to the total order value being greater than 100;
- "feedback has resonated positively" refers to the average rating of the products they have reviewed being greater than 3.

- "big spenders" refers to customers who have a high average price per item;
- "golden mark of 50" refers to an average price per item of more than 50;
- "more than one item per order" means the quantity of items in the order is greater than 1;
- "how much have they purchased in total" refers to the total number of items purchased by each customer.

- "shining stars" refers to brands with high performance in terms of customer base and revenue;
- "star products" refers to products that generate significant revenue;
- "customer satisfaction and loyalty" are measured by average ratings, number of reviews, and the frequency and value of customer purchases.

- 'Actively shining' refers to products with a status of 'active';
- 'Dispatched to their admirers' refers to orders with a status of 'shipped';
- 'Revenue-generating stars' refers to products that generate the most revenue;
- 'Top 3' means the highest-ranking products based on total revenue.

- "More than two recommendations" means a customer has recommended at least three products;
- "Most recent recommendations" are the latest recommendations based on the recommendation date;
- "Average rating" is calculated from all reviews for that product.

- "shining brighter than the average star" refers to brands whose total revenue is greater than the average total revenue of all brands;
- "favored shipping methods" refers to the shipping methods associated with these high-revenue brands, which have a high average order value;
- "carry the heaviest weight" refers to the highest average order values.

- 'top 5 brands' refers to the brands with the highest total order value and average customer rating;
- 'treasure trove of sales' refers to the total order value;
- 'highest praise from their customers' refers to the average rating of the reviews.

- 'Top-spending customers' refers to customers with the highest total order value;
- 'US or without a specified region' means customers from the US region or those whose region is not specified;
- 'Total order value' is the sum of the product of the quantity and price for each order item.

- "shining stars in the sky" refers to products that are highly rated (4 stars or more);
- "well-loved by customers" refers to products with a high number of positive reviews;
- "substantial revenue" refers to significant sales revenue from products priced at $20 or more.
